#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.63"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.63:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.63:0.2"
msgid "6. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "6. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.63:0.3"
msgid "63. Nibbedhikasutta "
msgstr "63. Penetrative "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.410, sc1
msgctxt "an6.63:1.1"
msgid "“Nibbedhikapariyāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you a penetrative exposition of the teaching. "

msgctxt "an6.63:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.63:1.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "an6.63:1.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an6.63:2.1"
msgid "“Katamo ca so, bhikkhave, nibbedhikapariyāyo dhammapariyāyo? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, what is the penetrative exposition of the teaching? "

#. VAR: kāmanirodho → kāmānaṃ nirodho (mr)
#. VAR: kāmanirodhagāminī → kāmanirodhagāmini (pts1) | kāmānaṃ nirodhagāminī (mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:2.2"
msgid "Kāmā, bhikkhave, veditabbā, kāmānaṃ nidānasambhavo veditabbo, kāmānaṃ vemattatā veditabbā, kāmānaṃ vipāko veditabbo, kāmanirodho veditabbo, kāmanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbā. (1) "
msgstr "Sensual pleasures should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an6.63:3.1"
msgid "Vedanā, bhikkhave, veditabbā, vedanānaṃ nidānasambhavo veditabbo, vedanānaṃ vemattatā veditabbā, vedanānaṃ vipāko veditabbo, vedanānirodho veditabbo, vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbā. (2) "
msgstr "Feelings should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an6.63:4.1"
msgid "Saññā, bhikkhave, veditabbā, saññānaṃ nidānasambhavo veditabbo, saññānaṃ vemattatā veditabbā, saññānaṃ vipāko veditabbo, saññānirodho veditabbo, saññānirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbā. (3) "
msgstr "Perceptions should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an6.63:5.1"
msgid "Āsavā, bhikkhave, veditabbā, āsavānaṃ nidānasambhavo veditabbo, āsavānaṃ vemattatā veditabbā, āsavānaṃ vipāko veditabbo, āsavanirodho veditabbo, āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbā. (4) "
msgstr "Defilements should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an6.63:6.1"
msgid "Kammaṃ, bhikkhave, veditabbaṃ, kammānaṃ nidānasambhavo veditabbo, kammānaṃ vemattatā veditabbā, kammānaṃ vipāko veditabbo, kammanirodho veditabbo, kammanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbā. (5) "
msgstr "Deeds should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an6.63:7.1"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ, bhikkhave, veditabbaṃ, dukkhassa nidānasambhavo veditabbo, dukkhassa vemattatā veditabbā, dukkhassa vipāko veditabbo, dukkhanirodho veditabbo, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbā. (6) "
msgstr "Suffering should be known. And its source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation should be known. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.411, sc8
msgctxt "an6.63:8.1"
msgid "‘Kāmā, bhikkhave, veditabbā, kāmānaṃ nidānasambhavo veditabbo, kāmānaṃ vemattatā veditabbā, kāmānaṃ vipāko veditabbo, kāmanirodho veditabbo, kāmanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbā’ti, iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Sensual pleasures should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ That’s what I said, "

msgctxt "an6.63:8.2"
msgid "Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "an6.63:8.3"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā—"
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "an6.63:8.4"
msgid "cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā, "
msgstr "Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "an6.63:8.5"
msgid "sotaviññeyyā saddā … "
msgstr "Sounds known by the ear … "

msgctxt "an6.63:8.6"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā … "
msgstr "Smells known by the nose … "

msgctxt "an6.63:8.7"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā … "
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue … "

msgctxt "an6.63:8.8"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

#. VAR: ca kho, bhikkhave, nete kāmā kāmaguṇā nāmete → te kāmaguṇā nāma nete kāmā (mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:8.9"
msgid "Api ca kho, bhikkhave, nete kāmā kāmaguṇā nāmete ariyassa vinaye vuccanti—"
msgstr "However, these are not sensual pleasures. In the training of the noble one they’re called ‘kinds of sensual stimulation’. "

# NOTE: I don’t follow BB’s treatment of this as prose. In addition to this context the verse is quoted with the extra line at Kv 8.3.sc9
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
msgctxt "an6.63:8.10"
msgid "Saṅkapparāgo purisassa kāmo, "
msgstr "Greedy intention is a person’s sensual pleasure. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Nete → na te (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.63:8.11"
msgid "Nete kāmā yāni citrāni loke; "
msgstr "The world’s pretty things aren’t sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.63:8.12"
msgid "Saṅkapparāgo purisassa kāmo, "
msgstr "Greedy intention is a person’s sensual pleasure. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.63:8.13"
msgid "Tiṭṭhanti citrāni tatheva loke; "
msgstr "The world’s pretty things stay just as they are, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.63:8.14"
msgid "Athettha dhīrā vinayanti chandanti. "
msgstr "but a wise one removes desire for them. "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an6.63:10.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ nidānasambhavo? "
msgstr "And what is the source of sensual pleasures? "

msgctxt "an6.63:10.2"
msgid "Phasso, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ nidānasambhavo. "
msgstr "Contact is their source. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an6.63:11.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ vemattatā? "
msgstr "And what is the diversity of sensual pleasures? "

msgctxt "an6.63:11.2"
msgid "Añño, bhikkhave, kāmo rūpesu, añño kāmo saddesu, añño kāmo gandhesu, añño kāmo rasesu, añño kāmo phoṭṭhabbesu. "
msgstr "The sensual desire for sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches are all different. "

msgctxt "an6.63:11.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ vemattatā. "
msgstr "This is called the diversity of sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an6.63:12.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ vipāko? "
msgstr "And what is the result of sensual pleasures? "

msgctxt "an6.63:12.2"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, kāmayamāno tajjaṃ tajjaṃ attabhāvaṃ abhinibbatteti puññabhāgiyaṃ vā apuññabhāgiyaṃ vā, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kāmānaṃ vipāko. "
msgstr "When one who desires sensual pleasures creates a corresponding life-form, with the attributes of either good or bad deeds—this is called the result of sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.412, sc13
msgctxt "an6.63:13.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, kāmanirodho? "
msgstr "And what is the cessation of sensual pleasures? "

#. VAR: Phassanirodho → phassanirodhā (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.63:13.2"
msgid "Phassanirodho, bhikkhave, kāmanirodho. "
msgstr "When contact ceases, sensual pleasures cease. "

msgctxt "an6.63:13.3"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo kāmanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of sensual pleasures is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "an6.63:13.4"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
#. VAR: Yato kho → yato ca kho (bahūsu)
msgctxt "an6.63:14.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ kāme pajānāti, evaṃ kāmānaṃ nidānasambhavaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kāmānaṃ vemattataṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kāmānaṃ vipākaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kāmanirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kāmanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, so imaṃ nibbedhikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pajānāti kāmanirodhaṃ. "
msgstr "When a noble disciple understands sensual pleasures in this way—and understands their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation—they understand that this penetrative spiritual life is the cessation of sensual pleasures. "

#. VAR: kāmanirodhagāminī → … gāmini (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.63:14.2"
msgid "Kāmā, bhikkhave, veditabbā … pe … kāmanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti, "
msgstr "‘Sensual pleasures should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:14.3"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (1) "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an6.63:15.1"
msgid "Vedanā, bhikkhave, veditabbā … pe … vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti, "
msgstr "‘Feelings should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:15.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "an6.63:15.3"
msgid "Tisso imā, bhikkhave, vedanā—"
msgstr "There are these three feelings: "

msgctxt "an6.63:15.4"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an6.63:16.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ nidānasambhavo? "
msgstr "And what is the source of feelings? "

msgctxt "an6.63:16.2"
msgid "Phasso, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ nidānasambhavo. "
msgstr "Contact is their source. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an6.63:17.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ vemattatā? "
msgstr "And what is the diversity of feelings? "

msgctxt "an6.63:17.2"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, sāmisā sukhā vedanā, atthi nirāmisā sukhā vedanā, atthi sāmisā dukkhā vedanā, atthi nirāmisā dukkhā vedanā, atthi sāmisā adukkhamasukhā vedanā, atthi nirāmisā adukkhamasukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "There are material pleasant feelings, spiritual pleasant feelings, material painful feelings, spiritual painful feelings, material neutral feelings, and spiritual neutral feelings. "

msgctxt "an6.63:17.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ vemattatā. "
msgstr "This is called the diversity of feelings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an6.63:18.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ vipāko? "
msgstr "And what is the result of feelings? "

#. VAR: vediyamāno → vedayamāno (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an6.63:18.2"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, vediyamāno tajjaṃ tajjaṃ attabhāvaṃ abhinibbatteti puññabhāgiyaṃ vā apuññabhāgiyaṃ vā, "
msgstr "When one who feels creates a corresponding life-form, with the attributes of either good or bad deeds—"

msgctxt "an6.63:18.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vedanānaṃ vipāko. "
msgstr "this is called the result of feelings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an6.63:19.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, vedanānirodho? "
msgstr "And what is the cessation of feelings? "

#. VAR: Phassanirodho → phassanirodhā (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:19.2"
msgid "Phassanirodho, bhikkhave, vedanānirodho. "
msgstr "When contact ceases, feelings cease. "

msgctxt "an6.63:19.3"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of feelings is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "an6.63:19.4"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.413, sc20
msgctxt "an6.63:20.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ vedanaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ vedanānaṃ nidānasambhavaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ vedanānaṃ vemattataṃ pajānāti, evaṃ vedanānaṃ vipākaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ vedanānirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ vedanānirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti. So imaṃ nibbedhikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pajānāti vedanānirodhaṃ. "
msgstr "When a noble disciple understands feelings in this way … they understand that this penetrative spiritual life is the cessation of feelings. "

msgctxt "an6.63:20.2"
msgid "Vedanā, bhikkhave, veditabbā … pe … vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti, "
msgstr "‘Feelings should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:20.3"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (2) "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "an6.63:21.1"
msgid "Saññā, bhikkhave, veditabbā … pe … saññānirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti, "
msgstr "‘Perceptions should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:21.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "an6.63:21.3"
msgid "Chayimā, bhikkhave, saññā—"
msgstr "There are these six perceptions: "

msgctxt "an6.63:21.4"
msgid "rūpasaññā, saddasaññā, gandhasaññā, rasasaññā, phoṭṭhabbasaññā, dhammasaññā. "
msgstr "perceptions of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "an6.63:22.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, saññānaṃ nidānasambhavo? "
msgstr "And what is the source of perceptions? "

msgctxt "an6.63:22.2"
msgid "Phasso, bhikkhave, saññānaṃ nidānasambhavo. "
msgstr "Contact is their source. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "an6.63:23.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, saññānaṃ vemattatā? "
msgstr "And what is the diversity of perceptions? "

#. VAR: bhikkhave, saññā rūpesu, aññā saññā saddesu → aññā bhikkhave rūpesu saññā aññā saddesu saññā (mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:23.2"
msgid "Aññā, bhikkhave, saññā rūpesu, aññā saññā saddesu, aññā saññā gandhesu, aññā saññā rasesu, aññā saññā phoṭṭhabbesu, aññā saññā dhammesu. "
msgstr "The perceptions of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts are all different. "

msgctxt "an6.63:23.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saññānaṃ vemattatā. "
msgstr "This is called the diversity of perceptions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "an6.63:24.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, saññānaṃ vipāko? "
msgstr "And what is the result of perceptions? "

#. VAR: Vohāravepakkaṃ → vohāravepakkāhaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: saññaṃ → saññā (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.63:24.2"
msgid "Vohāravepakkaṃ, bhikkhave, saññaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "Communication is the result of perception, I say. "

#. VAR: ahosinti → ahosīti (mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:24.3"
msgid "Yathā yathā naṃ sañjānāti tathā tathā voharati, evaṃ saññī ahosinti. "
msgstr "You communicate something in whatever manner you perceive it, saying ‘That’s what I perceived.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:24.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saññānaṃ vipāko. "
msgstr "This is called the result of perceptions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "an6.63:25.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, saññānirodho? "
msgstr "And what is the cessation of perception? "

#. VAR: Phassanirodho → phassanirodhā (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:25.2"
msgid "Phassanirodho, bhikkhave, saññānirodho. "
msgstr "When contact ceases, perception ceases. "

msgctxt "an6.63:25.3"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saññānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of perceptions is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "an6.63:25.4"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.414, sc26
msgctxt "an6.63:26.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ saññaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ saññānaṃ nidānasambhavaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ saññānaṃ vemattataṃ pajānāti, evaṃ saññānaṃ vipākaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ saññānirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ saññānirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, so imaṃ nibbedhikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pajānāti saññānirodhaṃ. "
msgstr "When a noble disciple understands perception in this way … they understand that this penetrative spiritual life is the cessation of perception. "

msgctxt "an6.63:26.2"
msgid "Saññā, bhikkhave, veditabbā … pe … saññānirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti. "
msgstr "‘Perceptions should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:26.3"
msgid "Iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (3) "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc27
#. VAR: āsavanirodhagāminī → sabbatthapi evameva
msgctxt "an6.63:27.1"
msgid "Āsavā, bhikkhave, veditabbā … pe … āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti, "
msgstr "‘Defilements should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:27.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "an6.63:27.3"
msgid "Tayome, bhikkhave, āsavā—"
msgstr "There are these three defilements: "

msgctxt "an6.63:27.4"
msgid "kāmāsavo, bhavāsavo, avijjāsavo. "
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "an6.63:28.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ nidānasambhavo? "
msgstr "And what is the source of defilements? "

msgctxt "an6.63:28.2"
msgid "Avijjā, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ nidānasambhavo. "
msgstr "Ignorance is the source of defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc29
msgctxt "an6.63:29.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ vemattatā? "
msgstr "And what is the diversity of defilements? "

#. VAR: nirayagamanīyā → nirayagāminiyā (bj, mr) | nirayagamaniyā (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.63:29.2"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, āsavā nirayagamanīyā, atthi āsavā tiracchānayonigamanīyā, atthi āsavā pettivisayagamanīyā, atthi āsavā manussalokagamanīyā, atthi āsavā devalokagamanīyā. "
msgstr "There are defilements that lead to rebirth in hell, the animal realm, the ghost realm, the human world, and the world of the gods. "

msgctxt "an6.63:29.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ vemattatā. "
msgstr "This is called the diversity of defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "an6.63:30.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ vipāko? "
msgstr "And what is the result of defilements? "

msgctxt "an6.63:30.2"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, avijjāgato tajjaṃ tajjaṃ attabhāvaṃ abhinibbatteti puññabhāgiyaṃ vā apuññabhāgiyaṃ vā, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ vipāko. "
msgstr "When one who is ignorant creates a corresponding life-form, with the attributes of either good or bad deeds—this is called the result of defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "an6.63:31.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, āsavanirodho? "
msgstr "And what is the cessation of defilements? "

msgctxt "an6.63:31.2"
msgid "Avijjānirodho, bhikkhave, āsavanirodho. "
msgstr "When ignorance ceases, defilements cease. "

#. VAR: āsavanirodhagāminī → sabbatthapi evameva
msgctxt "an6.63:31.3"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of defilements is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "an6.63:31.4"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.415, sc32
msgctxt "an6.63:32.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ āsave pajānāti, evaṃ āsavānaṃ nidānasambhavaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ āsavānaṃ vemattataṃ pajānāti, evaṃ āsavānaṃ vipākaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ āsavānaṃ nirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ āsavānaṃ nirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, so imaṃ nibbedhikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pajānāti āsavanirodhaṃ. "
msgstr "When a noble disciple understands defilements in this way … they understand that this penetrative spiritual life is the cessation of defilements. "

#. VAR: āsavanirodhagāminī → sabbatthapi evameva
msgctxt "an6.63:32.2"
msgid "Āsavā, bhikkhave, veditabbā … pe … āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti. "
msgstr "‘Defilements should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:32.3"
msgid "Iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (4) "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc33
#. VAR: kammanirodhagāminī → sabbatthapi evameva
msgctxt "an6.63:33.1"
msgid "Kammaṃ, bhikkhave, veditabbaṃ … pe … kammanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti, iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Deeds should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ That’s what I said, "

msgctxt "an6.63:33.2"
msgid "Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "an6.63:33.3"
msgid "Cetanāhaṃ, bhikkhave, kammaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "It is intention that I call deeds. "

msgctxt "an6.63:33.4"
msgid "Cetayitvā kammaṃ karoti—"
msgstr "For after making a choice one acts "

msgctxt "an6.63:33.5"
msgid "kāyena vācāya manasā. "
msgstr "by way of body, speech, and mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "an6.63:34.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, kammānaṃ nidānasambhavo? "
msgstr "And what is the source of deeds? "

msgctxt "an6.63:34.2"
msgid "Phasso, bhikkhave, kammānaṃ nidānasambhavo. "
msgstr "Contact is their source. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc35
msgctxt "an6.63:35.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, kammānaṃ vemattatā? "
msgstr "And what is the diversity of deeds? "

msgctxt "an6.63:35.2"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ nirayavedanīyaṃ, atthi kammaṃ tiracchānayonivedanīyaṃ, atthi kammaṃ pettivisayavedanīyaṃ, atthi kammaṃ manussalokavedanīyaṃ, atthi kammaṃ devalokavedanīyaṃ. "
msgstr "There are deeds that lead to rebirth in hell, the animal realm, the ghost realm, the human world, and the world of the gods. "

msgctxt "an6.63:35.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammānaṃ vemattatā. "
msgstr "This is called the diversity of deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "an6.63:36.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, kammānaṃ vipāko? "
msgstr "And what is the result of deeds? "

#. VAR: Tividhāhaṃ → imāhaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:36.2"
msgid "Tividhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, kammānaṃ vipākaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "The result of deeds is threefold, I say: "

#. VAR: diṭṭheva → diṭṭhe vā (bj)
msgctxt "an6.63:36.3"
msgid "diṭṭheva dhamme, upapajje vā, apare vā pariyāye. "
msgstr "in this very life, on rebirth in the next life, or at some later time. "

msgctxt "an6.63:36.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammānaṃ vipāko. "
msgstr "This is called the result of deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc37
msgctxt "an6.63:37.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, kammanirodho? "
msgstr "And what is the cessation of deeds? "

#. VAR: Phassanirodho → phassanirodhā (si, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:37.2"
msgid "Phassanirodho, bhikkhave, kammanirodho. "
msgstr "When contact ceases, deeds cease. "

#. VAR: kammanirodhagāminī → sabbatthapi evameva
msgctxt "an6.63:37.3"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo kammanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of deeds is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "an6.63:37.4"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.416, sc38
msgctxt "an6.63:38.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ kammaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kammānaṃ nidānasambhavaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kammānaṃ vemattataṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kammānaṃ vipākaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kammanirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ kammanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, so imaṃ nibbedhikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pajānāti kammanirodhaṃ. "
msgstr "When a noble disciple understands deeds in this way … they understand that this penetrative spiritual life is the cessation of deeds. "

msgctxt "an6.63:38.2"
msgid "Kammaṃ, bhikkhave, veditabbaṃ … pe … kammanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti, "
msgstr "‘Deeds should be known. And their source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:38.3"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (5) "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "an6.63:39.1"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ, bhikkhave, veditabbaṃ, dukkhassa nidānasambhavo veditabbo, dukkhassa vemattatā veditabbā, dukkhassa vipāko veditabbo, dukkhanirodho veditabbo, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti. "
msgstr "‘Suffering should be known. And its source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:39.2"
msgid "Iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

#. VAR: byādhipi dukkho → vyādhipi dukkho (bj) | byādhipi dukkhā (s1-3, mr) | vyādhipi dukkhā (pts1)
#. VAR: pañcupādānakkhandhā → pañcupādānakkhandhāpi (mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:39.3"
msgid "Jātipi dukkhā, jarāpi dukkhā, byādhipi dukkho, maraṇampi dukkhaṃ, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsāpi dukkhā, yampicchaṃ na labhati tampi dukkhaṃ, saṃkhittena pañcupādānakkhandhā dukkhā. "
msgstr "Rebirth is suffering; old age is suffering; illness is suffering; death is suffering; sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are suffering; not getting what you wish for is suffering. In brief, the five grasping aggregates are suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
msgctxt "an6.63:40.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhassa nidānasambhavo? "
msgstr "And what is the source of suffering? "

msgctxt "an6.63:40.2"
msgid "Taṇhā, bhikkhave, dukkhassa nidānasambhavo. "
msgstr "Craving is the source of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "an6.63:41.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, dukkhassa vemattatā? "
msgstr "And what is the diversity of suffering? "

msgctxt "an6.63:41.2"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ adhimattaṃ, atthi parittaṃ, atthi dandhavirāgi, atthi khippavirāgi. "
msgstr "There is suffering that is severe, mild, slow to fade, and quick to fade. "

msgctxt "an6.63:41.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhassa vemattatā. "
msgstr "This is called the diversity of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc42
msgctxt "an6.63:42.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhassa vipāko? "
msgstr "And what is the result of suffering? "

#. VAR: pariyādinnacitto → pariyādiṇṇacitto (mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:42.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco yena dukkhena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto socati kilamati paridevati, urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati, yena vā pana dukkhena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto bahiddhā pariyeṭṭhiṃ āpajjati: "
msgstr "It’s when someone who is overcome and overwhelmed by suffering sorrows and pines and cries, beating their breast and falling into confusion. Or else, overcome by that suffering, they begin an external search, wondering: "

#. VAR: ko → so na (mr)
#. VAR: jānāti → pajānāti (bj, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:42.3"
msgid "‘ko ekapadaṃ dvipadaṃ jānāti imassa dukkhassa nirodhāyā’ti? "
msgstr "‘Who knows one or two phrases to stop this suffering?’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:42.4"
msgid "Sammohavepakkaṃ vāhaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ vadāmi pariyeṭṭhivepakkaṃ vā. "
msgstr "The result of suffering is either confusion or a search, I say. "

msgctxt "an6.63:42.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhassa vipāko. "
msgstr "This is called the result of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc43
msgctxt "an6.63:43.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodho? "
msgstr "And what is the cessation of suffering? "

#. VAR: Taṇhānirodho → taṇhānirodhā (si, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an6.63:43.2"
msgid "Taṇhānirodho, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodho. "
msgstr "When craving ceases, suffering ceases. "

msgctxt "an6.63:43.3"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo dukkhassa nirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of suffering is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "an6.63:43.4"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.417, sc44
msgctxt "an6.63:44.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ dukkhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ dukkhassa nidānasambhavaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ dukkhassa vemattataṃ pajānāti, evaṃ dukkhassa vipākaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ dukkhanirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, so imaṃ nibbedhikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pajānāti dukkhanirodhaṃ. "
msgstr "When a noble disciple understands suffering in this way … they understand that this penetrative spiritual life is the cessation of suffering. "

msgctxt "an6.63:44.2"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ, bhikkhave, veditabbaṃ, dukkhassa nidānasambhavo veditabbo, dukkhassa vemattatā veditabbā, dukkhassa vipāko veditabbo, dukkhanirodho veditabbo, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā veditabbāti. "
msgstr "‘Suffering should be known. And its source, diversity, result, cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation should be known.’ "

msgctxt "an6.63:44.3"
msgid "Iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (6) "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc45
msgctxt "an6.63:45.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho so, bhikkhave, nibbedhikapariyāyo dhammapariyāyo”ti. "
msgstr "This is the penetrative exposition of the teaching.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.63:45.2"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

